public interface ISeriesListener<A extends Comparable<A>,O extends Comparable<O>>

Series listener. Most interaction within the framework is achieved by listening to series updates. The methods in this interface are called synchronously in the same thread, in the same order with which the listeners have been added. This is to maintain the minimum latency when reacting to new data. Execution of this method should therefore be very short and should never block. Any long or potentially blocking job must be carried out in a separate thread. Any exception should be catched inside the methods.
